docs.abstract: IBM said that Promontory, which advises banks on regulatory matters, would mesh with its own offerings, including its Watson artificial intelligence platform.
docs.snippet: IBM said that Promontory, which advises banks on regulatory matters, would mesh with its own offerings, including its Watson artificial intelligence platform.
docs.lead_paragraph: In recent years, IBM has been known for its forays into artificial intelligence and cloud computing. Now, the technology provider is moving deeper into financial consulting with the acquisition of a prominent — and at times controversial — Washington firm.

headline.main: IBM to Acquire Promontory, a Financial Consulting Firm
headline.print_headline: IBM Moves Deeper Into Financial Consulting With Promontory Purchase

byline.original: By Michael J. de la Merced

docs.abstract: Four people involved in the creation of an industry partnership say its intent will be clear: to ensure that A.I. research is focused on things that will benefit people, not hurt them.
docs.snippet: Four people involved in the creation of an industry partnership say its intent will be clear: to ensure that A.I. research is focused on things that will benefit people, not hurt them.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — For years, science-fiction moviemakers have been making us fear the bad things that artificially intelligent machines might do to their human creators. But for the next decade or two, our biggest concern is more likely to be that robots will take away our jobs or bump into us on the highway.

headline.main: How Tech Giants Are Devising Real Ethics for Artificial Intelligence
headline.print_headline: Devising Real Ethics for Artificial Intelligence

docs.abstract: As G.E., Oracle, Salesforce.com and others push their A.I. products, it remains unclear whether potential customers understand how they will profit.

docs.abstract: The Partnership on AI unites Amazon, Facebook, Google, IBM and Microsoft to ease public fears of machines that are learning to think for themselves.

docs.lead_paragraph: Five major technology companies said Wednesday that they had created an organization to set the ground rules for protecting humans — and their jobs — in the face of rapid advances in artificial intelligence.

headline.print_headline: Protecting Humans and Jobs From Robots Is 5 Tech Giants’ Goal

docs.abstract: Watson, the IBM computer platform that dominated on “Jeopardy!” and has helped fight cancer, is part of a pilot program that will help teachers build personalized lesson plans.
docs.snippet: Watson, the IBM computer platform that dominated on “Jeopardy!” and has helped fight cancer, is part of a pilot program that will help teachers build personalized lesson plans.
docs.lead_paragraph: It knew enough about medical diagnoses and literature to beat “Jeopardy!” champions at their game, and has been put to use in cancer wards. Now, an IBM computer platform called Watson is taking on something really tough: teaching third-grade math.

headline.main: Next Target for IBM’s Watson? Third-Grade Math
headline.print_headline: Fractions Next Target for Winner of ‘Jeopardy!’
